<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18073</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>72. For your information. Department just received following telegram
                            from American Consul, Piedras Negras: [Here follows telegram from Vice
                            Consul Blocker of May 7, 1916.]</p>
                        <p>Bring same to attention <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> authorities and
                            impress upon them seriousness of incident, especially at this time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>